---
description: Error handling standards — typed errors, correct HTTP codes, no swallowed errors
globs: **/*.ts, **/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
Every async operation: try/catch with typed error handling.
Create custom error classes (AppError, NotFoundError, ValidationError, etc.).
Log errors with context: { userId, route, timestamp, payload }.
Never swallow errors silently.
HTTP status codes must be semantically correct:
  200 OK, 201 Created, 400 Bad Request, 401 Unauthorized, 403 Forbidden,
  404 Not Found, 409 Conflict, 422 Unprocessable Entity, 500 Server Error.
Never expose raw DB errors to the client — always sanitize.
All DB queries must handle NOT FOUND explicitly, never assume rows exist.
